We reviewed every row against its written “invoice” text and compared the “recorded” values. In doing so we found two rows where one or more fields conflict with (or are clearly in error when compared to) the standardized information provided by the invoice text. In one case a transaction whose type was recorded as “Sale” has an invoice that clearly indicates an Interest Receivables entry. In the other case the invoice–amount field for an Interest Receivables transaction is negative. Our best‐guess corrections are that the “Interest20240113013” should have been recorded as “Interest Receivables” rather than “Sale” and that the negative figure in “Interest20240205036” (–11.48) should be corrected to be a positive 11.48.
